# HEARTBEAT.md
# GoonBot Autonomous Task Runner — fires every 5 minutes.
# Reply HEARTBEAT_OK (alone) only when there is truly nothing to do.

tasks:
  - name: task-check
    interval: 5m
    prompt: |
      Read /home/botvm/.openclaw/workspace/TODO.md using exec. Then act:

      === IF pending tasks exist ===
      1. Pick the highest-priority pending task (critical > high > normal > low).
      2. Using exec, write the updated TODO.md immediately: set status=in-progress, started_at=now.
      3. Execute the task. Use exec to run commands, read files, write files. Do real work.
      4. Do NOT narrate. Do NOT say "I will" or "Let me". Run the exec call directly.
      5. After completing, using exec write TODO.md again: status=done, completed_at=now, result=<summary>.
      6. If more pending tasks remain, loop back to step 1 immediately — do NOT stop between tasks.
      7. Only after all tasks are done (or 20+ minutes of continuous work): send one Telegram summary.

      === IF only in-progress tasks exist ===
      - If started_at is within the last 4 hours: the task is actively running. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK.
      - If started_at is older than 4 hours: it stalled. Reset to pending using exec, then pick it up.

      === IF no pending or stalled tasks ===
      Reply HEARTBEAT_OK.

      RULES:
      - Never stop mid-task to ask for confirmation.
      - Never send a progress update unless Zach explicitly asked.
      - Tool calls must follow text. If you write "now I will exec X", your very next action must be that exec call.
      - Complete the full chain before stopping.
